<section class="mission-details">
	<div class="mission-intro">
		
		<a name="eztoc19727243_1" id="eztoc19727243_1"></a><h2><b>The mission</b></h2><p>Carrying a suite of cutting-edge instruments, Copernicus Sentinel-3 measures systematically Earth’s oceans, land, ice and atmosphere to monitor and understand large-scale global dynamics. It provides essential information in near-real time for ocean and weather forecasting.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="mission-data">
		
		<a name="eztoc19728266_1" id="eztoc19728266_1"></a><h2><b>The launch</b></h2><p>
<b>Date:</b>&nbsp;Sentinel-3A on 16 February 2016<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Sentinel-3B on 25 April 2018<br />
<b>Site:&nbsp;</b>Plesetsk Cosmodrome, Russia<br /><b>Launcher:</b>&nbsp;Rockot</p>
	</div>
	</section>

